10k copies sold 🥹 

This might not seem like a lot, but when you consider that MFs don’t be reading, I don’t even have 100k followers, and didn’t spend a ton of money on marketing… this is huge. This was the arbitrary number I let live in my brain as an indicator that my book was doing “good”… and she IS! Thank you to every person who bought, downloaded, listens to, or checked out a copy of Notes From A Trap Feminist 😭😭😭

Ice on the cake when I bake it 🍰

Remember that time I dropped a mixtape? Well... I’m performing them for the first time (in public, the tape went platinum in the crib) next week! June 2 | 7pm | @thesultanroom | Brooklyn | Link to tickets and the tape in my bio! Swipe to the end for my official performance moodboard 👛🍬💅🏾

The next #aboutfacebeautystop is @bonnaroo from 6/15 to 6/18. Thank me later.

Reveling… Because this time last year was devastation; and what’s to come is beautiful, glorious, and lonely. 

But every version is fine AF which is probably why @dmissesjay & @dr_stacyann took 1000 shots 😂

I made a mixtape a couple years ago because I thought it was a cute gag to go with my book. I never intended on performing any of them, but @jewel_thegem asked me to, so I did. And I ATE! 

Ppl been asking me about this footage all month, even folks who saw the show in person… because I ATE. But I’ve been just sitting on it and was fully prepared to leave it in the vault because, wait for it… I don’t like the way I looked in the outfit 😑

…and now that I’ve typed it out, I can see how goofy I sound 😂 This was my first solo performance. I wrote every song, I performed over instrumentals, not vocal tracks, didn’t have a hype person or a DJ, and people knew the words. No tea no shade but it’s some girlies with record deals who would look better in this outfit, that still can’t do all that at a show 🤷🏾‍♀️
